    "files": {
      "KC-Golden-Retriever.pdf": [
        {
          "text": "Golden Retrievers\nBreed History\nThe Golden Retriever has long stood as one of the most\npopular dog breeds in the United States, and for many good\nreasons. Originally developed in the Scottish Highlands by\nthe first Lord Tweedmouth, this gundog was designed to\naccompany the sporting elite during long days of hunting.\nThese early examples of the breed performed the essential\ntask of swimming out to retrieve downed waterfowl. The\nmodern Golden Retriever belongs to the Sporting Group in\nthe American",
