        {
          "text": " Kennel Club\noutlines what tests are suggested for each breed to prevent\nthe continuation of genetic diseases. The recommended\nhealth tests for Retrievers include hip and elbow \nevaluations, and ophthalmic and cardiac exams. When\nmeeting the puppies, ask to see both parents and any other\nrelated dogs that may be on site. Both puppies and adult\nmembers of the breed should seem friendly and sociable, any\nsign of aggression (apart from a female with very young\npuppies) should be cause for concern. ",
