        {
          "text": "inually and forever watched over and protected. Most of the instincts that other breeds have for \nsafety or survival have long been bred out of the Pug. The average, well-bred, happy Pug is neither destructive nor is\nhe an avid digger or barker. When he does bark, it is with a softer more muffled tone than most dogs display. Pugs \nare not one of the breeds that require \u201ccontinual jobs\u201d or they become destructive. Once they are past teething age, \nthey do not have the long \u2018needy\u2019 teeth of the te",
