          "text": "splay some neurotic \nor obsessive tendencies occasionally.\nFor the true Pug lover, this behaviour just adds to the uniqueness and charm of the Pug. The Pug breed is a distinct, \nwonderful addition to the right home.\nPugs are Not Reliable\nYou must have a fenced yard that is secure for a small dog, or you must walk your Pug on a leash every time he \nneeds to relieve himself. Accompanying your Pug, off leash, in an open yard, is not acceptable. Pugs have a \n\u2018malady\u2019 that we Pug-folk have coined as ",
