        {
          "text": "ian cinema.[8]\n[9]\u00a0The\u00a0Government of India\u00a0honoured him with the\u00a0Padma \nBhushan\u00a0in 2000 and the\u00a0Padma Vibhushan\u00a0in 2016, India's \nthird and second highest\u00a0civilian honours\u00a0respectively, \nthe\u00a0Dadasaheb Phalke Award\u00a0in 2019, the highest Indian \naward in the field of cinema, and the\u00a0IFFI Satyajit Ray Lifetime \nAchievement Award\u00a0for his contributions to world cinema.[10][11]\nMajor centres of\u00a0film\u00a0production across the country \ninclude\u00a0Mumbai,\u00a0Hyderabad,\u00a0Chennai,\u00a0Kolkata,\u00a0Kochi,\u00a0\nBengaluru,\u00a0Bhubanesw",
