        {
          "text": "uction across the country \ninclude\u00a0Mumbai,\u00a0Hyderabad,\u00a0Chennai,\u00a0Kolkata,\u00a0Kochi,\u00a0\nBengaluru,\u00a0Bhubaneswar-Cuttack, and\u00a0Guwahati.[details 1]\u00a0For a \nnumber of years, the Indian film industry has ranked first in \nthe\u00a0world\u00a0in terms of annual film output.[28]\u00a0In 2024, Indian \ncinema earned\u00a0\u20b911, 833\u00a0crore\u00a0($1.36 billion) at the Indian box-\noffice.[5]\u00a0Ramoji Film City\u00a0located in Hyderabad is certified by \nthe\u00a0Guinness World Records\u00a0as the largest film studio complex \nin the world measuring over 1,666\u00a0acr",
