          "text": "the\u00a0Guinness World Records\u00a0as the largest film studio complex \nin the world measuring over 1,666\u00a0acres\u00a0(674\u00a0ha).[29]\nIndian cinema is composed of\u00a0multilingual\u00a0and\u00a0multi-ethnic\u00a0film \nart. The term 'Bollywood', often mistakenly used to refer to \nIndian cinema as a whole, specifically denotes the Hindi-\nlanguage film industry. Indian cinema, however, is an umbrella \nterm encompassing multiple film industries, each producing \nfilms in its respective language and showcasing unique cultural \nand styli",
