          "text": "dustries, each producing \nfilms in its respective language and showcasing unique cultural \nand stylistic elements.\nIn 2021,\u00a0Telugu cinema\u00a0emerged as the largest film industry in \nIndia in terms of box office.[30][31]\u00a0In 2022,\u00a0Hindi \ncinema\u00a0represented 33% of box office revenue, followed \nby\u00a0Telugu\u00a0representing 20%,\u00a0Tamil\u00a0representing \n16%,\u00a0Bengali\u00a0and\u00a0Kannada\u00a0representing 8%, \nand\u00a0Malayalam\u00a0representing 6%, \nwith\u00a0Marathi,\u00a0Punjabi\u00a0and\u00a0Gujarati\u00a0being the other prominent \nfilm industries based on r",
