        {
          "text": "enting 6%, \nwith\u00a0Marathi,\u00a0Punjabi\u00a0and\u00a0Gujarati\u00a0being the other prominent \nfilm industries based on revenue.[32][33]\u00a0As of 2022, the \ncombined revenue of\u00a0South Indian\u00a0film industries has \nsurpassed that of the Mumbai-based Hindi-language film \nindustry (Bollywood).[34][35]\u00a0As of 2022, Telugu cinema leads \nIndian cinema with 23.3\u00a0crore\u00a0(233 million) tickets sold, \nfollowed by Tamil cinema with 20.5 crore (205 million) and \nHindi cinema with 18.9 crore (189 million).[36][32]\nIndian cinema is a glob",
