        {
          "text": "crore (205 million) and \nHindi cinema with 18.9 crore (189 million).[36][32]\nIndian cinema is a global enterprise,[37]\u00a0and its films have \nattracted international attention and acclaim throughout\u00a0South \nAsia.[38]\u00a0Since\u00a0talkies\u00a0began in 1931, Hindi cinema has led in \nterms of box office performance, but in recent years it has \nfaced stiff competition from Telugu cinema.[39][31]\u00a0Overseas \nIndians account for 12% of the industry's revenue.[40]\n",
